	   <tr><td colspan=2>Um, actually, VI has only stated that Dex was used in Fletching. They've said that Strength is the secondary of Smithing. They've never announced anything for tailoring, jewelrycraft, pottery, baking, brewing, fishing, alchemy poison making or tinkering.<br><br>FYI: VI added STRENGTH to Smithing as a secondary stat because many melee classes that were smiths were having a difficult time because of their subpar INT/WIS. Because Skill ups depend on high INT/WIS (Whichever is higher), and most melee classes have low INT/WIS, they decided to add STR to that mix, making it INT/WIS/STR for smithing. It doesn't matter how high all three is, just your highest one.<br>For instance, if you have 100 INT, 76 WIS, and 214 STR, all rolls will be based on your strength, and will totally disregard your INT/WIS stats.<br>Same thing with DEX and Fletching. They added it for the same reason they added strength to the smithing tradeskill.<br><br>No other trades use alternatives to INT/WIS, and it all depneds on the highest Stat, not how high all three are.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Jarnin Fisheermann<br>58th Evoker<br>&lt;Ring of Cobalt&gt;<br>Rallos Zek</td></tr>
